<p class="p">We applied city-specific linear ERFs derived from Baccini et al. (
 <xref rid="c4" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">2008</xref>) for each of the 14 cities. The ERFs describe linear relationships between daily 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M32" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">max</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M33" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">mean</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> for Barcelona) and daily heat-related mortality in terms of relative risk (RR). RRs were reported by Baccini et al. (
 <xref rid="c4" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">2008</xref>) as a percentage change in mortality per 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M34" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    <mo class="mo">°</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">C</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> above the city-specific threshold temperature. We converted the RRs to RR ratios from 
 <disp-formula id="d2" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">
   <span xml:space="preserve" class="x" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">[</span>2
   <span xml:space="preserve" class="x" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">]</span>
  </label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="EHP634_d2.jpg" position="float" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M35" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mtext class="mtext">percentage</mtext>
     <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
     <mtext class="mtext">change</mtext>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mtext class="mtext">RR</mtext>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <mn class="mn">100</mn>
     <mo class="mo">.</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
